resources.string: Fuente de los amantes - Arq. Luis Barragan
The Los Clubes – Cuadra San Cristóbal y Fuente de los Amantes by architect Luis Barragan was built in Atizapán de Zaragoza, Mexico City in 1964-1969.
The Taj Mahal, an immense mausoleum of white marble, is the jewel of Muslim art in India built in Agra between 1631 and 1648 by order of the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his favourite wife.
Marina City is a mixed-use residential-commercial building complex in Chicago, Illinois, United States, North America, designed by architect Bertrand Goldberg.
The Sydney Opera House in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia, is one of the most famous performing arts venues in the world, designed by Pritzker Prize winning architect Jørn Utzon.
The Forbidden City in Beijing, China, is the largest ancient palatial structure in the world, constructed in 1420 and proudly displays the essence and culmination of traditional Chinese architecture
